Flow-through early-life stage toxicity tests were conducted with aldicarb... to determine /aldicarb/ effect on the survival and growth of fathead minnow (Pimephales promelas). Concn of 78 ug/l did not affect survival and growth. However, 156 ug/l /was/ lethal to larvae-juveniles exposed for 30 days posthatch. The maximum acceptable toxicant concn (MATC) of aldicarb for the fathead minnow is estimated to be between 78-156 ug/l.
